						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/S-T-Policy/Participatory-approaches-in-ARD/Related-developments/Benin-farmers-unite-against-effects-of-climate-change" title="Benin farmers unite against effects of climate change" alt="link">Benin farmers unite against effects of climate change</a></h2>

	
					<p>Farmers in Benin are implementing their own research findings to boost the soil fertility and moisture retention of their plots. The experiment is part of the project Strengthening the Capacity to Adapt to Climate Change in Rural Benin (PARBCC) - established in late 2007 - which aims to create a three-way conversation between farmers, meteorologists and the government, and help farmers make informed choices about when to sow and harvest crops. One of the long-term goals of the programme is to teach the farming community in Benin to mobilise itself to take action against the effects of climate change. Some 300 farmers are enrolled in sixty “field schools” across the country, working with researchers to help Beninese farmers cope with droughts, tropical storms and other hazards related to climate change. The project's aim is to develop, test and implement farming strategies suited to local conditions. These include mulching, planting pits, adopting integrated crop management and using organic fertilisers. (Source: Scidev.net, 13 October 2009)</p>
							<p><span class="date">4/11/2009</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/S-T-Policy/Participatory-approaches-in-ARD/Related-developments/Benin-farmers-unite-against-effects-of-climate-change">Read more...</a>
</div>
