						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/S-T-Policy/Participatory-approaches-in-ARD/Related-developments/Nigeria-Sensitises-farmers-on-cassava-production" title="Nigeria - Sensitises farmers on cassava production" alt="link">Nigeria - Sensitises farmers on cassava production</a></h2>

	
					<p> <i>The Tide Online</i>, 14 April 2006 | As part of efforts to sensitise rural women on cassava production and utilisation, the National Root Crops Research Institute (NRCRI) Umudike in Abia State has organised a training workshop on cassava for rural women. The institute Director, Dr. Kenneth Nwosu disclosed this during the review workshop last weekend.</p>
							<p><span class="date">22/05/2006</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/S-T-Policy/Participatory-approaches-in-ARD/Related-developments/Nigeria-Sensitises-farmers-on-cassava-production">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
</div>
</p>
						
						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/S-T-Policy/Participatory-approaches-in-ARD/Related-developments/Alemaya-University-in-Ethiopia-Conducting-210-Researches" title="Alemaya University in Ethiopia Conducting 210 Researches" alt="link">Alemaya University in Ethiopia Conducting 210 Researches</a></h2>

	
					<p> 26 July, 2004 | The Ethiopian Herald --  The Alemaya University said it has been undertaking 210 various researches with the participation of farmers since the beginning of this year. University President, Professor Belay Kassa told ENA that the researches being carried out at the university were in the areas of plant and animal sciences, Agro-engineering, Agro-Economics as well as agricultural dissemination, among others.</p>
							<p><span class="date">9/08/2005</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/S-T-Policy/Participatory-approaches-in-ARD/Related-developments/Alemaya-University-in-Ethiopia-Conducting-210-Researches">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
</div>
</p>
						
						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/S-T-Policy/Participatory-approaches-in-ARD/Related-developments/A-participatory-and-gender-responsive-approach-to-rural-households-and-resources" title="A participatory and gender - responsive approach to rural households and resources" alt="link">A participatory and gender - responsive approach to rural households and resources</a></h2>

	
					<p> Monday, 23 May 2005 | This pocket guide aims to assist extension and other community-based workers to understand the management of resources within and between rural households. It has been developed to assist people in applying a participatory and gender- responsive approach in their planning with and service to rural women and men. The guide promotes the SEAGA principles of giving priority to disadvantaged groups, focus on gender relations, and the use of participation and a holistic approach as essential in development work</p>
							<p><span class="date">7/06/2005</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/S-T-Policy/Participatory-approaches-in-ARD/Related-developments/A-participatory-and-gender-responsive-approach-to-rural-households-and-resources">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
</div>
</p>
						
						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/S-T-Policy/Participatory-approaches-in-ARD/Related-developments/NEPAD-FG-Raises-Panel-to-Assess-Development" title="NEPAD: FG Raises Panel to Assess Development" alt="link">NEPAD: FG Raises Panel to Assess Development</a></h2>

	
					<p> Monday, 23 May 2005 | The Federal Government has raised a national working committee to develop mechanisms for self-assessment of the country's development progress, under the New Partnership for African Development (NEPAD).</p>
							<p><span class="date">7/06/2005</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/S-T-Policy/Participatory-approaches-in-ARD/Related-developments/NEPAD-FG-Raises-Panel-to-Assess-Development">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
</div>
</p>
						
						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/S-T-Policy/Participatory-approaches-in-ARD/Related-developments/In-what-ways-will-civil-society-participation-contribute-to-influencing-outcomes-under-the-African-Peer-Review-Mechanism" title="In what ways will civil society participation contribute to influencing outcomes under the African Peer Review Mechanism?" alt="link">In what ways will civil society participation contribute to influencing outcomes under the African Peer Review Mechanism?</a></h2>

	
					<p> Mon, 23 May 2005 | This paper provides general information on the New Partnership for Africas Development (Nepad) and the African Peer Review Mechanism (APRM) in order to facilitate active participation in its processes. It draws on the Nepad policy documents, a range of commentaries and relevant survey data, and summarises key aspects of the Nepad vision and the APRM on the basis that they appear to be insufficiently clear to many individuals, organisations and legislatures potentially affected by them or interested in engaging.</p>
							<p><span class="date">7/06/2005</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/S-T-Policy/Participatory-approaches-in-ARD/Related-developments/In-what-ways-will-civil-society-participation-contribute-to-influencing-outcomes-under-the-African-Peer-Review-Mechanism">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
</div>
</p>
